).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE02E583F7D5A55FF741F00DBFFFB08" blockId="5.[136,1452,821,1207]" pageId="5" pageNumber="24">
Perennial plant with sterile shoots creeping, procumbent and rooting with green or glaucous linear and flattened leaves clustered in bundles at the apex. Flowering stems erect of 
<quantity id="4CA783BD3F7D5A55FC931F3CD987FBF4" box="[858,971,1073,1099]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="24" unit="cm" value="25.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="10.0">10–40 cm</quantity>
, reflexed before the anthesis, inflorescence without bracts, globose in bud; flowers (5) 6–7 (9) merous, obdiplostemonous, with pedicel of 
<quantity id="4CA783BD3F7D5A55FB3A1F58DF1AFBD0" box="[1267,1366,1109,1135]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 mm</quantity>
, sepals lanceolated and petals spreading, yellow lemon often with a green strip in the middle; filaments yellow and glabrous, styles erect at the anthesis.
</paragraph>
